      "amount": "1 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "salt",
      "amount": "1/2 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "black pepper",
      "amount": "1/4 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "lemon juice",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a large saucepan, heat the olive oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and sauté until translucent (about 5 minutes).",
    "Add the white cornmeal and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.",
    "Gradually add the chicken broth and water, whisking continuously to prevent lumps.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20-25 minutes.",
    "While the pilaf cooks, prepare the garnish by mixing together chopped parsley, dried mint, salt, and black pepper in a small bowl.",
    "When the pilaf is cooked, fluff it with a fork and stir in the lemon juice.",
    "Serve the Gülbi Pilavi hot, garnished with the herb mixture."
  ],
